    "body": "Nice catch @michaelsproul!\r\n\r\nIf there has been more than 1 fork version update in the last weak subjectivity period, then the following attack is possible:\r\n![eth2-fork-version](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25324105/83953369-ce1bab00-a7f4-11ea-831a-2ec0cbeb156d.png)\r\n\r\nIf the attacker is somehow able to replace 2/3rd of the validator set (from the starting point of the fork) in its chain, then the attacker can even make fork version updates to `X` and `Y` in that chain to cause even more confusion.\r\n\r\nTo avoid this attack, each fork version update block should be made a weak subjectivity checkpoint.",
